<DOC><DOCNO> AP880702-0044 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-02-88 0534EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     07-02 0382</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0390</SECOND><HEAD>Thunderstorms Rumble Through South</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Thunderstorms rumbled through Arkansas, west Texas, from Floridato the middle Mississippi Valley, through New England and westernWashington today while skies over much of the nation were clear.   A half dozen thunderstorms stirred up severe weather in theSouth on Friday night. In Arkansas, thunderstorms whipped highwinds that downed power lines in Little Rock and blew atractor-trailer off the interstate highway east of Mayflower. Athunderstorm in Alabama produced high winds that downed trees andpower lines around Mobile.   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstormsfrom the lower Missouri Valley through western, lower TennesseeValley and central Gulf Coast into central and southern Florida;scattered showers across northern and central New England andthrough the northern Pacific coast; and mostly sunny skies over therest of the nation.   Temperatures were forecast in the 70s or 80s across much of thenation; in the 60s across the northern two-thirds of New Englandand over northwest Washington; in the 90s from the northern Rockiesthrough the central and southern inter-mountain regions, acrosscentral and eastern Texas into the lower Mississippi Valley andacross the southern half of Florida; between 100 and 105 across theRio Grande Valleys of Texas; between 100 and 110 degrees from thevalleys of California into the desert Southwest.   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 45degrees at Marquette, Mich., Sault Ste Marie, Mich., and TraverseCity, Mich., to 89 degrees at Las Vegas, Nev.   Other reports:   _East: Atlanta 71 partly cloudy; Boston 53 cloudy; Buffalo 57fair; Charleston, S.C. 67 foggy; Cincinnati 57 fair; Cleveland 50fair; Detroit 54 fair; Miami 79 partly cloudy; New York 61 fair;Philadelphia 57 fair; Pittsburgh 54 fair; Portland, Maine 52 partlycloudy; Washington 62 fair.   _Central: Bismarck 62 cloudy; Chicago 61 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth83 fair; Denver 68 fair; Des Moines 64 cloudy; Indianapolis 63cloudy; Kansas City 61 cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 63 partlycloudy; Nashville 66 cloudy; New Orleans 79 fair; St. Louis 69cloudy.   _West: Albuquerque 72 fair; Anchorage 57 cloudy; Las Vegas 89fair; Phoenix 94 thunderstorms; Salt Lake City 77 partly cloudy;San Diego 63 fair; San Francisco 55 fair; Seattle 58 rain.   _Canada: Toronto 50 fair.</TEXT></DOC>